casebody.data:
In re VAN DYKE COPPER COMPANY, Debtor, Appellant. No. 8891. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 18, 1938. Francis D. Crable, of Prescott, Ariz., for appellant.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon application of appellant, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
